data.description: Come home to enjoy spacious, multi-generational living in this beautiful Dayton home!  The main portion of the house has a great-room encompassing the kitchen, dining, and living rooms.  Just off the great-room is the laundry & exit to the tandem 3-car garage.  The large master bedroom is in back and its associated bath boasts a separate shower stall, a garden tub, and a huge walk-in closet.  There is a second bedroom in this part of the home with another bath, available to the great-room as well. The real beauty of this home is the second apartment arrangement for another generation (mom and dad in their declining years or a youngster who wants his or her own space).  The "next-gen" apartment has a large main room, its own kitchen facilities (microwave, but no cooktop, plus a full-sized refrigerator), two bedrooms with a shared bath, and plenty of storage space.  It also boasts a private entrance and its own covered patio and separated back yard area.  If you don't have a second generation to share with, it would work as well for in-laws or even as a rental to help with the mortgage payments.  The apartment has separate heating and cooling controls for individual comfort preferences.  There is some new carpeting and a very large main back yard with an expansive covered patio and an uncovered pad for a gazebo and/or hot-tub with a walkway between the two.  The great-room has high ceilings and both the great-room and master bedroom have ceiling fans with elegant Tiffany-style lamps.  Both kitchens have granite counters and cherry cabinetry.  The appliances in the main kitchen are stainless, while the next-gen apartment has black appliances.  A partial security system (non functional at this point) exists with security cameras in several rooms - this potentially could be re-instated - and both entries to the separate units have keyless locking systems and can be programmed individually and uniquely.  There is room in the back yard for an RV parking space - all it needs is a gate in the fence to accommodate access.
